rComments: Amazing lecturer. Also, she has an  amazing derri√®re, for any guy/girl interested in such things.

You can get an A but it's definitely not a bird course. All the tasks and marking schemes are well defined, so you get what you put in. The material was very interesting to me. Dr. Dukewich is a great lecturer and puts a lot of effort into communicating in an interesting and clear way. I highly recommend going to her office hours for clarification.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Amazing lectures']

rComments: Very enthusiastic, knowledgable, there to explain and answer any questions no matter how long it takes. Extremely understanding , polite and fair. Exams where hard but were fair to the ones that had studied.

Professor Dukewich delivered very interesting lectures. Her passion for the field  really rub off on you :) She also puts a lot of effort into designing the course to ensure she could give the best learning experience. Tests were very fair and assignments were conducive to learning.  She's definitely a professor that students are lucky to have!
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Inspirational', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Not really good professor. Lecture slides are impossible to use for study, so make the notes. Tests are confusing, although the course itself is interesting.

Classes are filled with learning "tricks", such as forced participation at odd intervals in order to "solidify concepts" and odd noises to "grab your attention". If you have social anxiety, this class is stressful! Her slides usually have no information on them and are not a great study aid. Befriend your textbook, it will give you most of the info
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Get ready to read', 'Participation matters']

rComments: Pay attention in class then you won't need the textbook : )

She is super fair and puts so much effort into teaching . she really cares about her students. you need to study hard for heir courses . the only negatives were that she spoke too fast but its okay because she posts her recordings
Her slides are terrible and make no sense. I got a good grade after sticking to the textbook (even though she said it wasn't as important as her slides).

Be prepared for very tricky multiple choice. Even on the most minute small details from lectures she WILL test you on it. Always pay attention. Other than that, amazing classes with her. I always enjoyed the lectures. get okay grade anywhere from B+ to an A- in my experience. She's not for everyone though, be wary of that

LOVED the class, even though the class was tough. The prof is an energizer and is really engaging. I thought I hated the class at first because the material was kinda hard for me at first, but ended up loving the class by the end.
Honestly one of the hardest tests I've written at UofT, completely unfair, I'd like to see 20 year old Dukewich pass her tests

I don't know what's with the negative reviews. Maybe she's looked at them and improved. I personally think she gives amazing lectures. Lecture slides are clear, and they do help you remember! She explain concepts well, and gets sooo excited when someone asks a good question and stuff. Amazing prof! You'll have fun taking this course.
Her lectures were okay, but the tests were worded terribly. The written assignment was quite interesting though.

I was a first year student taking a second year class, so I was a little intimated but I loved this professor by the end! I found the tests a lot trickier than my other classes BUT she would take full responsibility for badly worded questions and woudn't count them :) This class was so interesting, and so was the prof! She actually cares
Mediocre prof. Terrible wording on midterms (MC), tests on technicalities. Slides contain very little info and speaks quickly. Very arrogant and stubborn with marking.

Dukewich is amazing! She is one of UofT's rare gems! She really cares about her students. She also incorporates research on learning & memory into her style of teaching. Yes, she is tough with deadlines, but she warns students about it in advance. Overall, Dukewich is one of my favorite profs at UofT. I'll never forget her or her PSY372 course.

Dukewich is a suitable Prof for this course. She is genuinely fascinated by this very practical subject. She brings worksheets and makes the class interactive for students. Not attending lectures will literally cost marks though. To do well on tests, you will need to attend lectures and will need the textbook to reenforce concepts.
Fantastic lecturer! Go sit through the lectures, even though recordings are provided. It's an engaging and rewarding experience.

Dukewich is a bubbly professor. Her personality is awesome and her classes are engaging. Also, her lecture slides are gorgeous. I will say her tests aren't the easiest.. but she will adjust the marks if she feels the questions were too difficult.

She is a great professor who is willing to help if you have any problems with the material.  Her tests are a little bit difficult and at times the wording of the questions were really confusing.  Her lectures are great and very interesting.
Nice and engaging prof

She gets a bad wrap because she can come across as rough, and she's a bit strict - but she's very reasonable and clear about those policies. Just hand stuff in on time. It isn't hard. Not to mention that she's infectiously engaging and enthusiastic. If you ask a question she can't answer, she'll often research it and get back to you. She's great!

Dr. Dukewich has a very infectious and enthusiatic personality that will rub off on you. She appears to genuinely enjoy teaching and the material. I also clearly remember coming late to one lecture and Dr. Dukewich waited before closing polling on iClicker to allow me to take the remote out and enter my vote. She is awesome.

Lovely woman, but she talks so fast that it is useless going to a lecture. She is such a strict enforcer of technicalities that instead of helping students grow, it lowers their grade dramatically. I'm talking 1 minute late is a %25 deduction. if you have something to hand in, GET THERE EARLY! and try for another professor teaching the same course.

She is very friendly and means well, so it pains me to say that she's just a terrible professor. I had her for two classes and  her lectures were boring and full of mistakes. Her tests were hit or miss, sometimes they were very easy but other times they were unfair in what they expected us to know.

Her mistakes can be explained by the fact that she is a really new professor. Of course she is going to make mistakes. She runs into trouble with math/science concepts, like the more physics parts of perception. She really cares for her students and despite the problems I thought she was an interesting, engaging professor.

She doesn't seem to know the material well, and seems like she's just reciting from something.  Her lectures are very confusing because she says things and puts words together that make her sound like she knows what she's talking about, but they don't actually make any sense.  The material's very interesting if you read the textbook.

unreasonable and unhelpful. openly condescending and down right rude. even when her marking scheme is wrong she is unwaveringly sticks with the wrong answers. our midterm started an hour late and her class dragged so slowly. horrible lecturer, horrible personality. i feel sorry for you if you ever have to take a class with her.
disorganized, not helpful, and clueless. Terrible experience taking this course.

She is a great prof who is able to explain the concepts of statistics extremely well and clear. Very interesting lectures and very helpful. She really cares for her students. Some mistakes throughout the semester due to her first time teaching the course, but I highly recommend her as a Stats prof!!!
Terrible teacher, extremely disorganized, prone to mistakes; I was very unhappy with this professor. She was also unclear about what she wanted to see on homework assignments.
